properties.areaDesc: Wind River Mountains West; Upper Green River Basin Foothills
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 15 at 3:43AM MST until February 16 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...More Snow for Western Wyoming Tonight through Sunday Night...

.A storm system will bring significant snow across much of western
Wyoming tonight through Sunday night.

* WHAT and WHERE...Snow expected. Snow accumulations will range
from 6 to 12 inches in the mountains. Snowfall of 2 to 4 inches
around Pinedale with 4 to 6 inches around Bondurant. Snowfall
around South Pass will range from 2 to 3 inches along with a
gusty wind.

* WHERE...Wind River Mountains West and Upper Green River Basin
Foothills.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 11 PM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult at times. Some blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility including South Pass.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Plan for adverse winter weather if
recreating this weekend.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 11 PM MST SUNDAY
